inn1.comm: Swing straightaway for Pathan. Full and on the off stump line, it swung away towards the slips
similar delivery and Gayle covers his off stump and shoulders arms.
slightly short of a length this time and again in that channel outside the off stump, Gayle pushes back and lets it go. Two slips in place
aiming for that wonder ball - the one that swings from leg and middle stump line and as usual, it doesn't and Gayle turns it off his legs to square-leg
full and swinging away again but this time Gayle doesn't flirt, lets it go to Dhoni. A great start from Pathan.
ooh! almost dragged that one back to stumps. Full and swinging away - late swing there and Morton drives without moving his feet and gets an inside edge
on a length, just outside the off stump, Morton comes forward and attempts to leave it but gets a outside edge, past gully
pushed across Gayle who stays adjacent to the line of the ball and shoulders his arms

gone! first strike to Agarkar! Pushed across Gayle who has a lame poke at it, and nicks it behind. A nothing shot, as they say and West Indies have lost the man who gave them a roaring start in the first game. India on the offensive here!
full-swinging delivery outside the off stump, left alone.

omg! almost a run-out there! Sarwan taps a short of length delivery close on the off side and goes for a run but Morton isn't impressed with the call and returns to his crease after initially starting to run. Yuvraj swoops in from the point, gathers the ball, makes a step or two forward and underarms a throw, misses and Sarwan dives back into his crease..

Got his man this time! full and it pitched on the off stump and straigthened towards the off stump and Morton went back and across but was surprised by the movement back into him and is trapped in front of the off stump. It would have taken the top of the off stump.
outside the off stump, shaping away and Lara lets it go
short of length, just outside the off stump and Lara has a flash at it, and gets a underedge and it rolls behind the stumps
on a length, around the off stump, Lara comes forward and pushes it to the off side
outside the off stump, left alone
another probing delivery outside the off stump, hint of away swing, no shot offered
another outswinger, left alone by Sarwan
this one came back in, defended back to the bowler
bit of width offered outside the off stump, cut away straight to the fielder at point
wayward delivery outside the off stump
driven straight to the fielder at cover point
drifting onto the pads, wrong line, Lara shuffles across a bit and flicks it away to the fine leg fence
short of a good length delivery, turned away towards square leg
short of length, on the legs, Lara tries to work it to the onside, doesn't connect and it rolls to the short fine leg
on  a length, outside the off stump, pushed to Yuvraj Singh at point
pushed across the left hander, left alone

ooh! short of a length, pitched on the middle stump and it straightened and Lara is caught in his shuffle and is rapped on his pads. Loud appeal goes up but the bounce might have saved him there. Lara yet to settle down
beaten outside the off stump! full and outside the off stump, shaping away and Lara has a flash at it, ends up playing outside the line
on a length, pushed across and Lara goes back and across and at the last minute decides to shoulder arms
on a length, and around the off stump, pushed to covers
on a length, slanting across and Sarwan gets back and across and has a jab at it. The ball keeps slightluy low and gets the edge before rolling over to point
on a length again but this time on the legs, tucked away to long leg
short, wide and slapped over point! Throws his hands at it and it screams to the point fence
almost an action replay there. Short and bit of width outside the off, and Lara who needs no invitation to have a go, cuts it but straight to Yuvraj at point
wide down the leg. Pathan tries to adjust his length and ends up pushing it too full and too much down the leg
on a length around the middle and leg stump line and veering towards the pads, tucked away to square-leg
super yorker! but Lara manages to dig it out

ooh! he almost had his man there! dropped by Raina at wide first slip! full and outside the off stump and Lara who goes back and across, ending up outside the off stump, pushes at it, away from his body. The edge flies low but straight to Raina who fails to hold on
full and Lara whips it off his leg but Sehwag , at square leg, dives to his left to make the stop
pushed across Lara but this time he lets it go.
full and pushed across him again, Lara leans forward and drives it to covers. Good looking shot but he doesn't find the gap.
driven down to mid-off, diving stop from Powar there cuts off a certain boundary
full and down the leg, Lara tries to whip it across, misses and is rapped on the pads.
full and driven through covers
comes forward to defend it watchfully
full and going down with the angle and Lara gets rapped on the pads again as he tries to whip it across.
just short of a length, pitched on the off and middle stump line and it came in slightly, Sarwan goes back and offers the full face of the bat in defence
well-disguised slower ball, full in length, on the legs, Sarwan tries to turn it on side, doesn't make contact, and it runs off the pads

appeal as Lara is hit on pads while shouldering arms. It pitched on the off stump, on a length, and shaped away ever so slightly and Lara makes a gutsy leave and the point of impact was outside the off stump
steered to third man
just short of a driveable lenght, outside the off stump, slapped hard to Kaif at covers who gets his body behind it and is hit on his knees.
short and rising outside the off stump, Sarwan shapes to pull but decides against it and lets it go
full and in the channel outside the off stump, Lara goes for a flamboyant cover drive, doesn't time it well and gets a inside edge
pitched on the leg and middle stump line, and veered towards the pads, turned to the on side
in the corridor outside the off stump, on a length, and Lara comes forward and shoulders his arms
similar delivery, inviting Lara to have a go, but he declines and lets it go

Got his man this time! Lara is out! lovely delivery that pitched on the off stump, on a length, and seamed away sharply. Lara, who had allowed the previous two balls to go through to the wicketkeeper, comes forward and has a poke at it. He tries to steer it through gully and is beaten by the movement and ends up edging to Dravid at first slip. The great batsman is gone and India are on top of things here
wide outside the off stump, leftalone
leading edge that fell short of covers! full and on the leg and middle stump line, Chanderpaul tries to work it through the onside but is beaten by the late swing
short and bit of width outside the off stump, Sarwan tries to square-cut, doesn't time it well and it rolls to point
beaten! peach of a delivery! full-length delivery, around the off stump and Sarwan is caught at his crease. He flashes at it,without moving his feet and is comprehensively beaten
beaten again! on a length this time, outside the off stump and shaping away and Sarwan ends up playing a nothing shot. a lame poke but luckily for him, doesn't connect
well outside the off stump, left alone
on the legs, Sarwan turns it to the onside and wants a run but sent back.
pushed across the right-hander, left alone
wide outside the off stump and angling away, left alone by Sarwan. Close to being called a wide
short of length, slanting away and Sarwan gets across and pushes it to point
full around the off stump, pushed to the off side
full and on the leg and middle stump line, Sarwan comes forward and ends up playing around his front pad a bit, and turns it to long leg
good length delivery outside the off stump, Sarwan gets forward and drives it down to mid-off, no room for a single there
good length delivery outside the off stump, bit wide and shaping away, Sarwan shuffles across a long way but in the end leaves it through to the keeper

short delivery outside the off stump and Sarwan neatly cuts it away towards point, Yuvraj there dives across full lenght to his right and cuts off a certain four - was in the ari and parallel to the gorund when he made contact, what a fielder!
driven into the gap between cover and mid-off, easy single
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, eased away towards cover
another line and length delivery, driven back to the bowler
tossed up and turning in, Sarwan on the back-foot looking to cut it away but the shot is not timed well enough and the ball rolls away off the bottom edge
on the stumps, turned away towards square leg
flighted delivery on the stumps, again turned away towards square leg but this time Sarwan gets it wide of the fielder and they scamper through for a single

take that! tossed up on the stumps, Chanderpaul comes down the track, for a moment it looked like he had mis-read the length but Chanderpaul went through with the lofted drive and the ball screamed away to the wide long-off fence, once bounce and over the ropes she goes
another lovely inside-out drive and the result is the same, this time he was more accurate with the waltz down the track
defended watchfully
on the middle and leg, turned away on the leg side
good length delivery outside the off stump, shaping away after hitting the deck and the ball zips past the outside edge, Sarwan beaten comprehensively
bit wide outside the off stump and Sarwan steers it down to third man for an easy single, much better shot
on the middle and leg stump line, turned away towards midwicket
short of a good length delivery, drifting down the leg side, Chanderpaul on the back-foot pulling but he misses the target by miles, ball clips the pads and rolls down to short fine leg
on the middle and off stump line, stroked away towards cover
pitched close to the off stump line and turning across, Chanderpaul stands tall on the back-foot and drives it away towards cover
cut away off the back-foot to the cover region, went straight to Kaif there but he failed to collect it properly, no damage done though
forced away off the back-foot to the point region
on the middle and off stump line, this is turning out to be a much better over Harbhajan, Chanderpaul is made to defend and the ball rolls away straight to Kaif moving in from the edge of the circle
driven through the gap between cover and mid-off, quick single taken
turned away towards square leg
good length delivery outside the off stump, lovely line and length, Chanderpaul leaves it through to the keeper
straighter delivery on this occasion, defended watchfully
again on the middle and leg stump line, defended on the back-foot and the ball rolls away on the leg side, Patel follows it up and cuts off the single
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, better line and length, Chanderpaul watchfully taps it away towards short cover
again on the stumps, tamely played back to the bowler, Chanderpaul being too cautious here?!
maiden! defended down on the leg side and a good over from Patel comes to an end
quicker delivery, drifting down the leg side and Sarwan fails to make contact, ball clips the pad and rolls away on the leg side
tossed up and turning in, defended on the front-foot

on the middle and off stump line, Sarwan leans well forward to the pitch of the delivery and clips it away through the hole between mid-on and midwicket, excellent wristy shot - runs hard and comes back for the second
again leans well forward and finds the gap between mid-on and cover, just a single on this occasion
tossed up on the stumps, defended watchfully

short and wide outside the off stump, a delivery filled with nothingness, Chanderpaul leans back and cuts it away in the air towards point, Kaif  there times his jump to perfection and pouches it safely - West Indies four down and in deep trouble here
driven straight to the fielder at mid-off
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven off the back-foot to the backward point fence, excellent shot under pressure
short ball and Sarwan ducks under it
turned away off the pads to the deep square leg region for a brace
eased away on the off side, Yuvraj at point moves across and picks it up
swing and miss outside the off stump, that was close
good length delivery outside the off stump and Sarwan hammers it over the in-field to the cover fence
on the middle and leg stump line, Samules ends up with an inside edge and the ball rolls away on the leg side
turned away nicely to the midwicket region
defended outside the off stump, well bowled Harbhajan
tossed up delivery, this one ripped the surface and turned in sharply, Samuels pushes forward and defends it away on the off side
flat delivery, Samules steps forward and drives it away well wide of the fielder at mid-on, easy single and Samules is off the mark
defended watchfully
good length delivery, close to the off stump line, driven away towards cover
another probing delivery outside the off stump, defended watchfully
harmless delivery but Samules tamely plays it away on the off side
short rising delivery, pitched outside the off stump and coming in with the angle, surprise delivery and Samuels had to battle hard to avoid getting hit, well bowled and equally well played.

take that! short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, Samuels gets a good stride in but fails to get close to the pitch, but he goes through with the drive and the ball rockets away through cover point, the ball was in the air for a long time but the fielders had no chance whatsoever
defended outside the off stump
driven wide of the cover fielder, easy two
turned away behind square on the leg side
bowled slower through the air, Samules drives it down to mid-on, no room for a single there
quicker delivery, Harbhajan mixing it up nicely here - Samuels reads it well, gets a good stride in and defends it down on the off side
on the stumps, driven back to the bowler
again tossed up on the stumps, defended straight back down the track, another fantastic over from Harbhajan comes to an end.
on the middle and leg stump line, turned away behind square, possible two but Sarwan happy with one!
quicker delivery, this time turned away straight to Yuvraj at square leg

played away off the back-foot to the point region, quick single called for, Sehwag moves across quickly, swoops low down and scores a direct hit at the bowler's end, loud appeal and the third umpire is woken up, Samuels had his bat nicely grounded when the ball hit the stumps - green light flashes
turned away behind square, this time the first run is taken quickly and Sarwan comfortably comes back for the second

flighted delivery outside the off stump, bit wide and Sarwan drives it away beautifully through the gap between the cover fielders, long chase ends in vain - kept the fielder interested till the end but eventually the ball trickled over the ropes
turned away on the leg side
defended on the front-foot
tossed up, driven back to the bowler
driven wide of the fielder at mid-off, easy single
turning in from close to the off stump line, Sarwan stays back and flicks it away well wide of the fielder at midwicket
quicker delivery to end the over, Samuels safely plays it away on the off side
starts off with a wide, drifting down the leg side and it's rightly called a wide
tossed up and turning in, Sarwan leans well forward and drives it down to long-on for a single
similar line and length and Samuels too drives it down to long-on for an easy single
quicker delivery on the pads, turned away well in front of square leg
driven down to long-on
fuller length delivery, driven straight back to the bowler
one again Powar gets the ball to turn back in from wide outside the off stump, Samuels stays back and works it away towards midwicket
tossed on the off stump line, tucked behind the square-leg
on the off and middle stump line, turned to short midwicket
driven to right of Harbhajan who dives to make the stop
pitched outside the off stump and it broke back in sharply, worked to short-leg
tossed on the middle, driven back down the pitch
flatter, quicker and shorter in length, pushed to the on side
well flighted just outside the off stump, pushed to short midwicket
slower this time and again on the off stump, turned to midwicket
floated up full and driven to long-on
on the middle and turning in, turned to the on side
good ball! flighted outside the off stump, Samuels dances down the track and is beaten by the flight and ends up pushing the ball to Yuvraj at square-leg
full and Samuels comes forward, to the pitch of the ball and works it to the on side
dances down the track and drives it back down the pitch
flatter this time and pushed to short midwicket where Kaif makes the stop
flat again, short of length, Samuels goes back, stands tall and punches it down to long-on
much slower this time, pitched outside the off stump and Sarwan is beaten on the forward prod. it rolls off the pads to the off side
on the legs, squeezed behind to fine-leg and they run hard to take two
tossed on the off stump line, full in length, Sarwan comes forward, bat and pad together and smothers the spin.
floated outside the off stump, Samuels comes down the track and drives it to long-off where Munaf makes the stop
comes forward to the pitch of the ball and works it through the midwicket
comes down the track and tries to go over the top and is beaten by the flight and it rolls to the on side
Powar drags that one a bit short, Samuel makes room by moving to the on side and cuts it past point
swept to the fine-leg  boundary
tossed outside the off stump, driven to Sehwag at long-off
on the legs, turned to long leg
slightly short and it pitched on the off and middle, turning in towards legs, tucked to fine-leg
slower and flighted outside the off stump, Sarwan comes forward, reaches out and square-drives it over covers
driven uppishly to long-off.
on the leg and middle, and it straightens after pitching and batsman is squared up a bit and the leading edge runs to covers
flatter and on the off stump, pushed to covers
cut to covers
tossed on the middle stump line, pushed back to the bowler
well-flighted delivery and driven back to the bowler
on a length, just outside the off stump and pushed to right of covers and they pinch a single
on the off stump line, full in length, pushed to point. A very good over there from Powar. Has he finally got his line right?
on the middle and leg stump line, turned to short midwicket
flatter and quicker - the arm ball, driven, bit uppishly, to the right of midwicket
turns in from outside the off stump, cut to point
pushed down the leg side and Sarwan is beaten as he attempts to glance and almost falls outside the crease. Dhoni doesn't gather it cleanly though
pushed to Agarkar in the off side ring
sliding down the legs, turned to fine-leg. And Harbhajan has finished his parsimonious spell.
full and on the leg and middle stump line, driven to short midwicket
driven out to long on. slower and full in length.
tossed outside the off stump, turning in and sarwan whips it to midwicket
tossed up again, much slower and Sarwan comes down the track but the ball dips sharply and he tries to work it to the on side, doesn't connect and is rapped on the pads
turned behind square-leg
on the leg and middle stump line, hint of spin, pushed back down the track
similar delivery and Sarwan comes forward and defends it watchfully

comes down the pitch and drives it through mid-on and that's fifty for Sarwan. Its been a painstaking one but importantly he is still there. It's certainly not his best knock! has looked out of touch actually.
plays a inside out drive to long-off

gone! beautiful work by Dhoni! It pitched on the off and middle stump line and Samuels backs to the leg a bit and tries to cut but is beaten by the extra bounce and Dhoni, moving towards his left, pouches it safely. And what's more whips off the bails as Samuels falls outside the crease, just in case the catch was not given!
on the legs, tries to glance, doesn't connect
driven past a diving Powar to long-off
well-flighted delivery, turning in from outside the off stump, pushed to the off side
lovely delivery! a drifter that hung in the air, almost eternally and batsman is beaten in the flight and mis-times a drive to mid-off

Wonderful catch by Raina at short midwicket! tossed outside the off stump, it drifts further away and Bravo, who had come down the track,  tries to whip it from outside the off stump and mistimes his flick-drive and Raina dives forward and to his left to come up with a superb catch
on the leg stump line, pushed back down the track
tossed on the middle stump, pushed to the off side
comes down the track and gets outside the line of the ball and drives it to long-on
flatter and on the leg and middle stump line again, pushed to the off side
tossed on the middle stump this time, driven out to deep cover where Powar makes the stop
on the legs, turned past square-leg

fuller length delivery, Sarwan ends up with an inside edge onto the pad and the ball rolls behind, Sarwan lost sight of the ball for a second but recovered quickly, Dhoni swoops low down clips it onto the stumps - third umpire called for - it's a touch and go scenario, in the end the batsman gets the benefit of doubt
turned away well wide of the fielder at square leg, easy single
on the stumps, turned away on the leg side
turning in from outside the off stump, Baugh rocks back, goes low down and cuts it away towards third man, takes on the fielder in the deep and makes it across for the third, well run
driven down to long-on
defended on the front-foot, another good over for India comes to an end
on the middle and off stump line, Sarwan taps it away towards cover point, played with soft hands and they scamper through for a single
shot! fraction short and drifting down the leg side, Baugh gets into a good position and pulls it away to the vacant fine leg fence, bad delivery put away in style
on the middle and off stump line, Baugh is caught in two minds and in the end plays a nothing shot, ball rips past the edge
defended on the back-foot
on the stumps, defended on the front-foot and the ball rolls away towards point
four more! Yuvraj once again drifts down the leg side and this time Baugh sweeps it away fine, more of a paddle sweep than a genuine sweep
slightly short, cut away off the back-foot and the ball goes straight to the fielder at point
pushed back to the bowler, not a well timed shot
turned away on the leg side
flatter trajectory, tempting delivery and Sarwan is sucked forward into the drive, ball clips the outside edge and races away to the third man fence
awkward shot, ball clips the pad and rolls away behind the stumps
turning in, Sarwan goes back and drives it away well wide of the fielder at cover, Patel cleans up in the deep
cut away off the back-foot to deep backward point, Pathan hurtles across in the deep and scores a direct hit at the striker's end but Baugh was never in trouble.
wayward delivery outside the off stump and the umpire is not happy with the width
Baugh on the attack now! good length delivery outside the off stump and Baugh hits on the up, ball flies away to the extra cover fence, good clean hit - West Indies on the move now - about time too.

played away behind point and they take off for a suicidal run, actually the mix-up turned it into a suicidal run - Yuvraj had all the time in the world, he lines up nicely and throws, any other day that would have been the end of Sarwan - but not today!
good length delivery, close to the off stump line, eased away on the off side
cut away to deep third man for a single
called for overstepping, finally the score board is on the move.
clipped away off the pads to the fine leg fence, this is exciting stuff from Baugh
turned away towards square leg, no room for a single there
again eased away on the leg side
finally he manages to get it past the fielder at square leg, two more added to the total
on the middle and leg stump line, driven down to long-on for a single
again turned away towards square leg

and Baugh departs! long-hop from Powar, Baugh rocks back and pulls hard, gets under it a bit and the ball balloons up towards deep midwicket, Pathan runs in from the deep and nicely settles under it - West Indies seven down
worked away off the pads to the square leg region

driven away off the back-foot to the point region, Sarwan takes off for a single but Bradshaw stands his ground, once again Yuvraj had all the time in the world but he misses the stumps at the bowler's end, Patel could have got behind the stumps and effected the run-out but for that you have to try...!
defended down on the off stump, bit of edge involved
beaten outside the off stump, excellent delivery from Patel
forced away towards deep square leg
driven wide of the fielder at mid-on
turned away to midwicket, fielder moves across and cuts off the single
defended down to short fine leg
cut away off the back-foot and the ball goes wide of the fielder at point
defended outside the off stump, was a well flighted delivery, Bradshaw defends it back to the bowler
defended back to the bowler
worked away through midwicket
bang! good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Bardshaw gets forward and lofts it down to the vacant long-on fence, powerful bowl
tucked away off the pads to the fine leg region
good length delivery, tight line and leght, Sarwan can do nothing but force it away towards cover
driven wide of the fielder at mid-off
well bowled yorker, Bardshaw jams his bat down and the ball rolls away towards the slip cordon
off the pads to the short fine leg region
fulltoss on the middle and leg stumps line and Bradshaw clips it away to deep midwicket, takes on Sehwag in the deep and they make it across for the second
turned away off the pads to long-leg

good length delivery outside the off stump, Sarwam makes room, probably looking to go inside out but fails to connect, infact he had to leave the ball alone as he backed-away too wide  - ball goes through to the keeper
yorker on the stumps, driven straight to Dravid at extra cover
driven down to long-off, easy single
beaten outside the off stump, good delivery to end the over
slower delivery, Sarwan goes for it, ball falls short of the fielder at short fine leg, close
way outside the off stump, Bradshaw had a swing at it missed the target by a long way
good length delivery outside the off stump, shaping away a touch, Bradshaw waits for the ball and at the last moment steers it through the vacant gully region

on the middle and off stump line, Bradshaw has a swipe across the line and the ball flies down to long-on, Harbhajan moves in from the deep and takes it cleanly - Bradshaw too departs, trying to force the pace - West Indies eight down
driven wide of the cover fielder, easy single
another run-out chance missed! turned away towards midwicket and they taken off for a single that was never there, this time it's Dravid who fails to hit the stumps at the bowler's end
driven away towards cover, quick single taken

cracking shot! good length delivery outside the off stump, Sarwan comes down the track and plays a flamboyantly adventurous inside-out drive, ball hits the middle of the bat and flies away to the cover fence, one of the hardest shot in the book but Sarwan made it look easy
worked away on the leg side, quick single taken
good length delivery outside the off stump, Taylor has a wild slash at it and the ball zips past the outside edge
pitched up and angling in, driven down to mid-off and the single brings Sarwan back on strike

good length delivery outside the off stump, Sarwan drives off the front-foot and the ball races away to sweeper cover, nicely opened the face of the bat at the point of impact to get it past the fielder inside the circle
punched down to mid-off and they go for the single
well disguised slower delivery and Taylor is beaten comprehensively

good length delivery, angling across - Taylor pushes forward and strokes it away towards point, quick single called for and Sarwan makes it across safely, Rain with the throw, needless to say that it missed the stumps!  direct hit would have been fatal
Sarwan! good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Sarwan comes down the track and hammers it inside-out to the wide long-off fence, desperate dive in the deep from Harbhajan ends in vain
another one! another decent delivery, this time on the middle and leg stump line, Sarwan stays back and slaps it away to the midwicket fence
and it gets bigger! fuller length delivery on the stumps, Sarwan comes down the track, takes it on the full and murders it over the long-on fence, crowd goes wild!
driven away to deep cover, end of a massive for West Indies
comes down the track and drives it down to long-on, they go for the single
Taylor too joins the party! under pressure Agarkar pitches it up outside the off stump and Taylor flays it away to the cover fence, clean hit
on the stumps, driven down to long-on and the single brings Sarwan to the fore
driven straight to Dravid at cover, quick single taken

Agarkar hits back for India! good length delivery, close to the off stump line, Taylor for starters steps away in an effort to make room, but changes his mind, basically he lost it totally and in the end it was a nothing shot, faint edge produced and Dhoni takes a good low catch - West Indies nine down
played away towards midwicket, just a single there- Sarwan stranded on 98 and West Indies end up with 198 on the board.

inn2.comm: beaten outside the off stump! Good ball first up, full in length and holding its line and Dravid ends playing inside the line
full and pushed out to the off side
full again, on the off stump line, Dravid comes forward and ends up playing bit ahead of his body, pushes it back down the pitch
on a length, but well outside the off stump and shapes away, Dravid lets it go.
nice delivery, full and just around the off stump, holding its line and Dravid again doesn't cover the line completely, just pushes it to the off side
on a length, outside the off stump and Dravid lets it go. Very good start from Edwards.
full and pushed across Sehwag who comes forward and drives on the up to mid-off
just short of length, pitched on the leg and middle stump line and going towards the off stump, Sehwag pushes back, and whips it off his hips to left of long-leg
And the first no-ball for West Indies. They bowled quite a few extras in the first game. Short and wide outside the off stump and Sehwag has a flash but misses.
short of length, on the off stump, Sehwag opens the face of his bat, turns it to point
arrgh! misfield at mid-off! Sehwag drives gloriously past the bowler and Samuels gets across but just rolls over the ball.
swing and a miss! full and slanted across, Sehwag flashes at it but ...
full and sliding down the legs, Sehwag tries to force it away, doesn't connect and it clips the pads enroute to Baugh, the wicketkeeper.
And a wide! hmm... sliding down the leg side. Audible sighs heard around the arena!
full and on the pads, Dravid puts his left foot across and plays around his front pad to push it to the on side
on a length, pitched just outside the off stump and moving towards the off, Dravid offers the full face of the bat in defence.
full and just outside the off stump and Dravid ends up playing outside the line a bit and gets an inside edge onto his pads
full and on the middle stump line, Dravid whips it across to the on side
super shot! full and on the middle and off stump line, Sehwag just stands and drives it on the up past the bowler and Taylor makes a diving stop at the ropes
short of a length, on the off stump, Sehwag hops back and pushes it to covers
slanted across Dravid who covers his off stump and lets it go to the keeper
just short of a length and angling across Dravid who waits on his back foot and cuts it to third man fence. Nice looking stroke
pushed to mid-on and they take a quick single
on a length, around the off stump and Dravid stands up tall and punches it back down the pitch. It takes out the stumps on the other end
pushed across Sehwag who comes forward to tap it towards covers.
short of a length and just outside the off stump, Sehwag waits, and then just steers it past gully

ooh! short of length and outside the off stump and Sehwag moved back and across and carved it, in the air, past guly and bradshaw, at the thirdman position, moves quickly to his left and makes a diving stop
short and rising towards chest high, on the off stump line, Sehwag uses his wrists and slaps it across to midwicket area
drifting down the legs, why oh why would you bowl to Dravid at his pads, and picked through the midwicket gap.
better ball this time, full and just outside the off stump and Dravid comes forward and pushes it quietly down to the off side.
on a length but well outside the off stump and Dravid flashes at it - square drives on the up, and the ball screams to the cover fence
on a length, slanting across, Sehwag shapes to play down the ground and is squared up a bit but adjusts and pushes it to the off side
on the middle and leg stump and Sehwag hops back to force it to midwicket
full and pushed across the right-hander, Sehwag tries to drive it on the up but doesn't time it and it takes the edge and runs to the on side
slightly slower and just outside the off stump, Sehwag waits and places it to the extra cover

gone! great catch by Dwayne Smith at point! short of length and angled across sehwag who ends up searching for the ball a bit and ends up playing on the walk. He plays a push-drive on the up and it goes in the air towards Smith who runs a few steps forward and dives in front to come up with a very good catch
beaten outside the off stump! short of a length and holding its line a bit, and Pathan has a lame poke at it
on the hips, turned behind square-leg
yorker! but well dug-out by Pathan. West Indies are fighting hard here!
short and wide, swing and a miss from Pathan. Tries to cut but is beaten by the extra bounce
good ball, on the off stump line and Pathan comes forward to push it to covers
pitched on the leg and middle stump line and held its line, turned to the on side
comes forward and defends it watchfully to the off side
on a length, around the off stump, pushed out to covers
short of length, worked away off the stumps to square-leg. Pathan wants a run but Dravid sends him back, the throw misses the stumps but Pathan was in the crease by then
outside the off stump, inviting Pathan to have a go, remember he was caught poking out in the first game, but this time he declines and lets it go
full-length delivery, on the off stump, Pathan comes forward and drives it back down the pitch
similar delivery, driven out to covers
slower one, outside the off stump, Pathan comes forward and punches it to point
drifting down the leg side, tickled past  square-leg
ooh! Swing and a miss! width offered outside the off stump and Pathan tries to crash it through covers, doesn't connect
pitched right up, driven past the bowler
on a length, slanting across Pathan who leans forward and punches it to covers
super cut! short of a length and just outside the off stump, Pathan goes back and across and plays a delightful horizontal cut shot past point
on a length, and Pathan pushes it back down the pitch
hit the deck hard, short of a length and rising, Pathan stands up tall and punches it down to the off side
fuller this time and on the off stump and Pathan square-drives it past point

gone! short of a length delivery, angled across, Dravid pokes at it, a uncharacteristic shot, gets an edge and is swallowed by Baugh, the wicketkeeper. he went searching for that ball, outside the off stump. Two down and the pressure is on now!
wide outside the off stump, left alone.
on a length, around the middle and off stump line, Yuvraj comes forward and punches it to wide of mid-on and gets off the mark
good-length delivery, on the off stump, pushed out to covers
short and bit of width offered outside the off stump, Pathan goes for a cut but this time is beaten by the lack of bounce
pushed out to covers where Lara makes the stop
hmm.. slower one, well outside the off stump, could have been called a wide but ..
beaten outside the off stump! Yuvraj has a poke at a short of length delivery, angled across him
on a length, around the middle and the off stump, turned towards midwicket
short of length, pitched on the middle stump line and shaping away, Yuvraj turns it towards mid-on
short of length again, and on the middle stump line, Yuvraj hops back and whips it square-leg where Bravo moves quickly to his right
this time yuvraj manages to use his wrists to play it finer on the on side, to the left of Bravo
on a length and it kicked up a bit from the leg stump line, squaring up Pathan who manages to adjust and pushes it to the off side
beautiful cover drive! Driven on the up, left elbow high, leaning into his drive and the ball screams to the cover fence
outside the off stump, left alone by Yuvraj Singh
slightly slower and on the off stump line, yuvraj thrusts his left foot out, bat and pad together, and pushes it to covers
pushed out to point, they look for a run but decide against it

oh! a run-out chance missed! full and just outside the off stump, Yuvraj comes forward, steers it to backward point and they take a quick single. Bravo, at point, moves to his right and has a shy at the stumps and if he had hit, Pathan would have been dead
on a length, just outside the off stump, pushed out to off side
on the legs, turned to fine-leg
short of length, angled across, Pathan push-drives it to point region
slapped past point! full and outside the off stump and square-driven to point fence
slower one and on the leg stump line, breaking in a bit and Pathan is squared up a bit, and it runs to the off side.
Ah! back to swing and a miss! full and outside the off stump, inviting Pathan to have a go, he does but doesn't connect. Now over to you Sajan!
on the middle and leg stump line, turned away towards midwicket and they scamper through for a qucik single, Smith's shy at the bowler's end stumps missed the target by a big margin
good length delivery, close to the off stump, forced away towards mid-off
short and wide outside the off stump, angling across, Pathan has a slash at it and gets beaten by a long way, unnecessary shot
pitched up further, close to the off stump line and Pathan drives it down to mid-off
line and length delivery, Pathan is made to defend and the ball rolls down to silly mid-off

there it is! good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, angling across the left-hander, Pathan comes down hard on it and the ball flies away towards wide midwicket, Samuels there dives across to his left and takes a blinder, was in the air when he took the catch and held on well even though he hit the deck hard
on the pads, Yuvraj flicks but fails to connect, ball clips the pad and rolls away towards midwicket
on the middle and leg stump line, played down the track to the mid-on region
short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, Yuvraj leans back and strokes it down to third man for an easy single
off the mark first ball, good length delivery on the pads, Kaif stays back and works it away right into the gap between mid-on and midwicket

good length delivery outside the off stump, angling across, Yuvraj shuffles across and drives on the up, nicely opened the face of the bat at the point of impact and got it through the gap between cover and point, easy two
on the middle and off stump line, Yuvraj stands tall on the back-foot and drives it straight back along the carpet to the mid-off reigon
called for overstepping, good length delivery outside the off stump, cutting in, defended on the front-foot
probing delivery outside the off stump, defended watchfully
defended on the back-foot
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, slanting across the left-hander, Yuvraj gets a good stride forward and forces it down to mid-off
low fulltoss on the off stump line, probably the yorker gone wrong, Kaif picks it up early and slaps it away to fine leg for a single
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, slanting across the left-hander, Yuvraj gets a good stride forward and jabs it down to mid-off
forced away towards cover point, watchfully played
slightly short and close to the off stump line, defended on the front-foot

fuller length delivery on the middle and off stump line, angling in, Kaif gets forward and punches it straight back past the bowler to the long-on region, Chanderpaul gives chase from mid-on and kicks the ball in, from right in front of the ropes and that combined with the relay throw saves two runs
good length delivery, driven away towards cover
good delivery from Taylor, defended down on the off side
another decent delivery from Taylor, Kaif watchfully plays it away towards cover
on the middle and off stump line, no movement whatsoever, Kaif ends up defending it back to the bowler

Taylor bangs one in short, bit of a surprise delivery and Kaif falls into the trap! ball skidded across after hitting the deck and Kaif looking to pull it away through midwicket ends up with a top-edge, ball balloons up towards square leg and Smith nicely settles under it, Another crucial wicket and it's game-on here!
good length delivery on the stumps, defended on the back-foot - good delivery first up
another one on the stumps, defended back to the bowler
driven away towards cover
short of a good length delivery, again on the middle and off stump line and angling across, Raina stays back and forces it away towards cover

Lara! good length delivery outside the off stump and Raina creams it away into the gap between the cover fielders, that ball was screaming away to the fence but a brilliant full length dive from Lara cuts short the journey - excellent commitment from the captain and the crowd is right behind the home team now!
defended on the back-foot and the ball rolls away towards mid-on
peach of a delivery, slightly short, pitched on middle and off and shaping away late, Yuvraj is cut into two and the ball zips past the outside edge
driven down to mid-on
line and length, defended on the back-foot
good length delivery outside the off stump, Yuvraj gets a good stride in and drills it through cover point, excellent shot under pressure

on the middle and off stump line, ball stopped a bit and Yuvraj is beaten by the lack of pace, mis-timed dirve and the ball goes in the air towards mid-on, but falls just short of the fielder there - it's all happening here
driven wide of the fielder at mid-on for an easy single, much better shot on this occasion
short of a good length delivery on the stumps, defended on the back-foot
powerful drive and the ball races away towards cover, another brilliant diving stop from Lara there cuts off yet another boundary - take a bow!
punched away well wide of the fielder at mid-off
driven away towards cover, good looking shot but Raina failed to get it past the fielder there

not this time though! short of a good length delivery, close to the off stump line - Raina steps forward towards the ball and swats it away through midwicket for a powerful boundary - now that's a positive shot!
defended outside the off stump
starts off with a quicker delivery on the stumps, defended on the front-foot
driven back past the diving bowler to the long-on region
on the stumps, eased away on the leg side
full and on the stumps, bowled from round the wicket, Yuvraj ends up playing it back to the bowler
driven straight back down the track to long-on, easy single
tossed up outside the off stump, driven down to long-off, yet another easy single added to the total
good length delivery, close to the off stump line, defended down to mid-off
pitched up outside the off stump, driven well wide of the fielder at cover and they stroll across for a single
driven well to the mid-off region, excellent bit of fielding there saves runs
good length delivery outside the off stump, driven away well wide of the fielder at point and they cross over

good length delivery outside the off stump, Yuvraj pushes forward and drives hard, ball clips the edge and races away through gully, desperate dive in the deep from the fielder moving across from third man ends in vain - more of a flashing kiss, bit of frustration creeping in
tucked away through square leg, easy single to end the over
defended outside the off stump
quicker delivery outside the off stump, played away towards gully and they scamper through for a single
tossed up close to the off stump line, defended watchfully
another quicker delivery from Gayle, defended leaning well forward
defended on the leg side
bit fuller and Raina drives it away well wide of the fielder at cover
driven down to mid-off
tossed up and turning across, defended on the front-foot
turn and bounce and Yuvraj is beaten there, thick edge and the ball rolls away well wide of the fielder at slip
quicker and flatter, defended watchfully
driven straight back down the track, diving stop from Samuels saves runs, good over so far
played away off the pads to the midwicket region, Samuels starts off with decent over
driven wide of the cover fielder, easy single
tossed up on the stumps, bowled from round the wicket, defended outside the off stump
worked away on the leg side
tossed up on the stumps, bowled from round the wicket, defended outside the off stump
driven down to long-on
pushed out to long-on
fired in the off stump, pushed to left of point and they scramble through for a single
slower, but again on the off stump line, Raina opens in his stance a bit and swats it to long-off
driven to long off
driven off the back-foot, out to long-off
ooh, almost a run-out! pulled to the right of midwicket where Samuels makes a diving stop and hurls in a throw at non-strikers end where Yuvraj makes a flying return to crease
pushed to covers
hit uppishly to the right of the bowler, out to long-off
full and on the middle and leg, Yuvraj plays a inside out drive to cover
tossed on the off stump, driven back to the bowler
drifting down the leg side.
defeneded off the front foot, out onto the off side
dragged it short and pulled to deep midwicket
cut to right of Morton, who makes a good diving stop and fires in a throw
full and driven out to mid-on
beaten on the forward prod, it rolls off the pads
defended off the front foot, back down the pitch
on the leg and middle stump line, full in length, driven out to long-on
slower and just outside the off stump, pushed to backward point
driven powerfully on the off side and Lara, at covers, moves to his right and makes a diving stop.
pushed to left of point and 100 is up for India! 99 more required
yorker length, on the middle stump, dug out
another one almost on the blockhole, driven out to long-on
driven straight to covers
down the leg and Raina goes down on his knee to sweep it fine leg
tossed on the leg and middle stump line, Yuvraj comes forward and turns it behind square-leg
slightly shorter, on the leg and middle, short-arm jabbed to right of midwicket and a good diving stop. West Indies are prowling like tigers on the field. Fabulous stuff!
slower, pitched on the off and broke away, steered to short thirdman region
down the leg side, Yuvraj tries to sweep, doesn't connect
down the leg side again, another sweep shot attempted, misses and it clips the pads enroute to the keeper
shorter and outside the off, cut past point
ooh! beaten outside off! pitched outside and turned away, Yuvraj tries to steer it through slips, misses
gets the inside edge onto the pads, off a forward prod
drifting down the leg side, turned behind square-leg. Drinks have been called
steered to backward point
beaten! turn and bounce! it pitched on the middle and leg and spins past the bat of Raina
flatter, pushed to long-on
Now its the turn of Yuvraj to get beaten outside the off stump. tries to steer it through slips but ...
driven powerfully back down the pitch
full and outside the off stump, steered to right of point
slower and outside the off, played with soft hands towards point and they take a single
tossed up, on the middle, pushed out to covers
full and on the middle, Raina tries to back away and pull, doesnt time well and gets a inside edge onto his pads. Not the length to play that shot
outside the off stump and Raina punches it off the backfoot to deep cover
on the legs, turned behind square-leg
on the leg and middle stump line, driven out to long-on
on the off, turning slightly away, steered to backward point
full and outside off stump, steered again to backward point
on the pads, worked behind square-leg
fuller and on the off stump, driven out past cover
quick yorker outside the off stump, through to the wicketkeeper
short, on the off stump, cut to point
short again, and pulled to deep midwicket. A chance for a boundary missed there.
much slower this time, drifting towards the pads, worked fine down the leg and they run hard to take two
on the legs again, turned to long leg
tossed up outside the off stump, pushed to point
Stumping chance missed! Raina dances down the track and yorks himself and misses, rather gets a inside edge, and it kisses past the glove of Baugh, going between the stumps and the keeper.
gone! West Indies get that important breakthrough. Raina dances down the track and ends up playing a pick-up shot, straight to Chanderpaul at long-off! Dhoni is in!
punched back down the pitch
pushed to the on side
tossed up outside the off stump, bowled from round the stumps, Yuvraj stays back and taps it away towards gully, Dhoni turns down the call
quicker delivery, drifting down the leg side, Yuvraj fails to make contact
defended outside the off stump
comes down the track and plays it away in the air and just wide of the fielder at midwicket, that was close
fraction short, pitched on middle and off stump and turning in, Dhoni rocks back and slaps it straight back to the bowler
flighted delivery on the middle and off stump line, turned away towards short midwicket
fuller and drifting onto middle and leg, Dhoni stays back and paddles it down to fine leg
driven down wide of the fielder at mid-off, easy single
driven down to long-off

and he does it! short of a good length delivery, close to the off stump and cutting in, Dhoni cuts off the back-foot with no real foot-work, ball clips the inside edge and crashes into the woodwork, Taylor pulls out a rabbit and the crowd goes wild - what a wicket!
glided down to third man and he is off the mark first ball
way down the leg side, poor delivery from Taylor
defended on the front-foot, ball rolls back to the bowler
swing and a miss outside the off stump, Yuvraj there beaten by the angle - bowler goes up for a caught behind but the keeper was not interested, so was the umpire
short of a good length delivery, angling across, driven away towrds cover
good length delivery, again angled across the left-hander, Agarkar gets forward and drives it down to long-off for an easy single
beaten! good length delivery outside the off stump, Yuvraj on the back-foot driving and the ball goes past the outside edge, well bowled
fifty! good length delivery outside the off stump and Yuvraj steers it down to third man for a single, excellent innings under pressure

another one bites the dust! this is unbelievable stuff from West Indies! clever change of pace and Agarkar played the sitting-duck act to perfection, on the middle and leg stump line, Agarkar pushes forward to defend and is beaten by the lack of pace, ball lobs back towards silly mid-on, Bradshaw on his follow through moves across quickly, dives forward full length and takes a stunning catch under pressure
beaten outside the off stump, excellent delivery first up.
turned away towards square leg, easy single brings Powar on strike
off the mark, full and on the pads, turned away behind square on the leg side, well played
on the stumps, punched down to mid-on
good length delivery, angling across, Yuvraj gets forward and defends it back to the bowler

take that! short and wide outside the off stump, bad delivery to say the least, Yuvraj cuts late and the ball races away to the backward point fence, sweetly timed and the fielder in the deep had no chance whatsoever - excellent shot to break the ice
another short delivery, angling across, Yuvraj neatly steers it down to third man, easy single and he will retain the strike, clever cricket this, from the south-paw.
fraction short and close to the off stump, Yuvraj cuts late but fails to make contact, beaten by the lack of bounce there
short and angling across, cut away off the back-foot to the third man region
good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, defended on the front-foot
edged down to third man
driven down to long-on
defended watchfully
another dot ball, end of a good over from Bradshaw
MAX! short ball outside the off stump, Yuvraj stands tall on the back-foot and pulls it away over the midwicket fence, got right under the bounce and timed it to perfection, Yuvraj is on a roll here
driven down to long-off, easy single and India inch closer to the target
good length delivery outside the off stump, Powar drives off the front-foot and the ball goes over Lara at cover, only just - that was a dangerous shot but he gets away with it
pitched up on the middle and leg stump line, clipped away to fine leg for a single
another single! good length delivery, Yuvraj shuffles back and punches it well wide of the fielder at midwicket

lucky! good length delivery outside the off stump, Powar looking to steers it down to third man gets nowhere with the tap shot but the ball clips the outside edge and races away to the third man fence, Taylor ends up with his hands on the head!
pushed to backward point
punched back down the track. No close in fielder
short and outside off, cut fine past the diving short third man fielder for couple of runs
take that! short and bit of width outside the off stump, under cut over point for a crucial boundary. Yuvraj is turning on the heat here
full and outside the off stumo, driven out to deep cover
fired in on the leg stump, Powar tries to whip it away, doesn't connect and it rolls to the on side
short of length, on the middle and leg stump line, Yuvraj stands tall and turns it fine to the short fine-leg region
on a length, around the off stump, pushed to extra cover.
slower ball! full and on the leg and middle stump line, Powar comes forward, waits and turns it behind square-leg
full and on a length, Yuvraj leans forward and drives it to mid-on.
ooh! swing and a miss! full and angled across, Powar thrusts his left foot out and has a almighty heave!
on the legs, tucked away to long leg. The singles are coming. Lara will have to do something to prevent this leakage
on the middle and leg, turned to midwicket
tossed on the leg and middle again, worked straight to short fine leg. Dot ball
another dot ball! again on the middle and leg, turned straight to short fine-leg again!
slightly short, outside the off, steered to short third man
steered straight to short third man. And so it will be Powar on strike for the next over.
short and well outside the off stump but Yuvraj misses a chance to crash it, hits it straight to point.
full and coming in towards the off stump, and yuvraj tries to whip it to on side, and the it rolls off the pads to the thirdman fence
beaten on the forward prod but gets a inside edge which takes the ball to shortish fine-leg and they take a run!
full and on the leg and middle stump line, driven to midwicket.
oh ho! beaten outside the off stump, pushed across Powar who tries to cut, but doesn't connect.
outside the off stump, yuvraj tries to play a inside-out drive, misses
tossed on the middle stump and driven out to long-on

gone! Another twist in the tale here! Crowd are on thier feet as Powar holes out to long off. He came down the track and Samuels, fires it in slightly short and Powar ends up mistiming his lofted shot.
fired in outside the off stump, Yuvraj tries to cut and is beaten
driven towards mid-off and by the time Samuels gets across to make the stop, they scramble through for a run. Now Harbhajan on strike!
fired in a yorker and well dug out by Harbhajan.
wide called! well outside the off stump and Yuvraj tries his best to reach but misses!  nerves showing here!
full and on the block hole length, driven out to covers and they take a run. Harbhajan is on strike. should be fun!
full and swinging in late, on the legs and Harbhajan is rapped on the pads and it runs down to shortish fine-leg.
sliced away past point , just a run though as Bradshaw hustles in and fires in a throw. Very good cricket all round.
another yorker attempted, and Harbhajan digs it out and even as the ball rolls off the inside edge to the keeper, they run through for a single!
omg! almost a run-out! yuvraj pushes it right of point and wants a run, sent back by Harbhajan and yuvraj just about reaches back in time
take that! Four! Yuvraj Singh, stands tall and drives a full-length delivery gloriously past the bowler for a crucial four. Yuvraj doing it here for India!

gone!!  Brilliantly caught and bowled by Gayle! Drama here at Sabina Park! Harbhajan pushes back tamely, a nothing shot, to right of Gayle who takes a step to his right and flings himself in the air to come up with a low catch.  Game on a knife edge here!
on the middle stump, Munaf pushes it to midwicket. No run but he survives.
fired in on the off stump, pushed out to covers
played back down the track. Another dot ball! Its getting mighty close!
tucked away behind square and they scramble through for a run
tossed on the off stump, just outside in fact and Yuvraj tries to paddle it around for a single, doesn't connect well and it rolls off the pads.

Fires in a yorker but it drifts on the legs, Munaf tries to dig it out, misses and gets a inside edge to the keeper and they scramble through for the vital run that brings yuvraj back onto the strike. 10 off 5 balls! What will Yuvraj Singh do?!
lucky four! Yuvraj makes room outside the leg stump and tries to hoick it across the line, gets a top edge and it flies just to left of baugh who tries his best to get a hand but .... Game on!

OMG! a crashing drive through covers for four! short of length delivery on the stumps, Yuvraj moves away from the stumps, towards the leg side and swats it over cover point for a vital four. 2 runs to win! can yuvraj maintain his cool and can Bravo do it for West Indies?

That's it! Game over! West Indies have won! Bravo does it for them, He slips in a slow yorker and Yuvraj comes forward and tries to whip it through the on side, doesn't connect and the furniture is disturbed! Sensational scenes here at Sabina Park! West Indies have won!
